value.value: 直腸脱
downward movement and external appearance of the rectum through the anus
盲腸の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the large sac at the ileum and large intestine junction
結腸の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the portion of the large intestine between the cecum and the rectum
小腸の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the portion of the digestive tube between the stomach and the cecum, consisting of the duodenum, ileum and jejunum
小腸の配置異常
different location or arrangement of the small intestinal tract
空腸の欠如
missing portion of the small intestine that extends from the duodenum to the ileum
回腸の欠如
missing portion of the small intestine that extends from the jejunum to the colon
小腸脱

the descent of the small intestine through a weakness in the supporting tissues at the apex of the vagina gives rise to an enterocele, frequently caused by a weakness or separation of the cardinal and sacro-uterine ligaments
消化液分泌の異常
anomaly in the production and/or release of a physiologically active substance (usually but not exclusively in liquid form) from a cell or a gland of the digestive system
消化液分泌の過剰
increase in the production and/or release of a physiologically active substance (usually but not exclusively in liquid form) from a cell or a gland of the digestive system
消化液分泌の減少
reduction in the production and/or release of a physiologically active substance (usually but not exclusively in liquid form) from a cell or a gland of the digestive system
消化液分泌の欠如
failure to produce and/or release a physiologically active substance (usually but not exclusively in liquid form) from a cell or a gland of the digestive system
右側異性

anomaly in the asymmetry of the visceral paired organs (e.g. lungs) such that organs on the left and right side have the morphology normally seen on the right side of the body; this may also be associated with absence of the spleen
弛張性腸出血
loss of blood from the intestines that is characterized by temporary periods of abatement
腸管粘膜の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the mucous lining of the intestine; this consists of epithelium, lamina propria, and a layer of smooth muscle cells
腸潰瘍
lesions in the mucous lining of the intestine
泌尿器系の形態異常

any structural anomaly of any of the organs or tissues responsible for fluid volume regulation, regulating electrolytes, maintaining acid-base homeostasis, and elimination of water and water soluble waste products in an organism
水腎症
dilation of the pelvis and calices of one or both kidneys
腎臓の欠如
absence of the two excretory organs that filter wastes (especially urea) from the blood and excrete them and water in urine
腎皮質の異常

any structural anomaly of the outer portion of the kidney located between the renal capsule and the renal medulla and involved in ultrafiltration; it contains the renal corpuscles, the renal tubules (except for parts of the loop of Henle which descend into the renal medulla), blood vessels and cortical collecting ducts
腎皮質の嚢胞
presence of one or more abnormal membranous sacs in the kidney cortex
腎皮質の糸球体症
any disease of the capillary plexus in the kidney cortex
尿細管数の減少
fewer of the loops of Henle, the proximal convoluted tubules or the distal convoluted tubules
尿細管性アシドーシス
a clinical syndrome characterized by the inability to acidify urine
髄質内錐体の矮小化
reduced size of pyramidal masses; contain part of the secreting tubules and collecting tubules
腎臓の発生異常
any anomaly in the differentiation of the paired organs responsible for urine secretion
腎臓の発生遅延
late onset of the induction and/or differentiation of the kidney
腎臓の脈管構造異常
any structural anomaly of the network of tubes that carries blood through the organ of excretion
肺の右側異性
anomaly in the asymmetry of the lung such that the lobes on both the left and right side have the morphology normally seen on the right side of the body
腎臓脈管のうっ血
obstruction of the normal flux of blood within the blood vessel network of the organ of secretion
腎出血
bleeding in the organ of excretion
尿管の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the tube that conducts the urine from the renal pelvis to the bladder
尿管管腔の肥厚
increase in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the ureter urothelium, typically resulting in increased size
水尿管
distention of the ureter with urine, due to blockage from any cause
尿道の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the fibromuscular tubular canal through which urine is discharged from the bladder to the exterior via the external urinary meatus; in males, the urethra is joined by the ejaculatory ducts and serves as a passageway for semen during ejaculation, as well as a canal for urine during voiding; in females, the urethra is shorter and emerges above the vaginal opening
膀胱の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the distensible musculomembranous organ that serves to collect and store urine excreted by the kidneys
膀胱拡張
stretched musculomembranous organ that serves to collect and store urine excreted by the kidneys
膀胱移行上皮の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the epithelial lining of the luminal space of the urinary bladder
左側異性

anomaly in the asymmetry of the visceral paired organs (e.g. lungs) such that organs on the left and right side have the morphology normally seen on the left side of the body; this may also be associated with the presence of multiple spleens
膀胱移行上皮の欠如
missing the transitional epithelial layer of the urinary bladder
薄い膀胱移行上皮
decrease in the thickness of the transitional epithelial layer of the urinary bladder
四肢の短縮
reduced average length of the extremities
四肢の伸長
increased average length of the extremities
四肢の欠如
absence of the projecting paired appendages of an animal trunk, used in particular for movement and grasping; usually denotes the arm and/or legs in mammalian species
前肢の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the projecting rostral-most paired appendages of an animal trunk, used in particular for movement and grasping; usually denotes the arm or front limb in mammalian species
前肢の欠如
absence of the projecting rostral-most paired appendages of an animal trunk, used in particular for movement and grasping; usually denotes the arm or front limb in mammalian species
橈骨の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the short bone of the lateral forearm
橈骨の欠如
missing the short bone of the lateral forearm
手根骨の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the nine nodular bones of the joint between the forelimb bones and the front paws/hands consisting of the scapholunar, triangular, greater multiangular, lesser multiangular, capitate, hamate, centrale and the sesamoids

definition.value: Note that the bony structure of the human and rodent carpals are different.

value.value: 手根骨の欠如

absence of any or all of the nine nodular bones of the joint between the forelimb bones and the front paws/hands, consisting of the scapholunar, triangular, greater multiangular, lesser multiangular, capitate, hamate, centrale and the sesamoids

definition.value: Note that the bony structure of the human and rodent carpals are different.
